cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.HC

This paper involves the use of neural networks for classification, which suggests it could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) suggests it could also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning and classification, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of EEG signals and brain-computer interfaces suggests it could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
